  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "rniuOEYdaygZ6hLwy3hn93cNm8g=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Vetra Studio consists of two main components:\n\n1. **Vetra Studio Drive** - A hub for developers to access, manage, and share specification documents through a visual interface. Each specification document corresponds to a module (document model, editor, data integration) that is a building block of your package.\n2. **Vetra Package Library** - A registry at vetra.io/packages for storing, publishing, and forking package repositories.\n\nVetra Studio runs inside **Connect**, the Powerhouse host application. When you run `ph vetra --watch`, it starts a local Reactor, launches Vetra Studio, and watches for specification changes to trigger automatic code generation.\n\nVetra supports three modes:\n- **Interactive mode** (`--interactive`): Confirmation prompts before code generation\n- **Watch mode** (`--watch`): Dynamic reloading for document-models and editors\n- **Standard mode**: Automatic processing with 1-second debounce",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
    }
  },
